# Cloud Agent Subagent Model Policy

When this repository is being worked on by a **Cursor Cloud Agent**, you MUST follow these rules for every `Task` / subagent spawn:

## Required model

- **Only** spawn subagents with model `cursor-grok-4.5-high`.
- Do **not** spawn subagents with any other model (including `cursor-grok-4.5-high-fast`, Composer, GPT/Codex, Claude, or the parent default when it would resolve to something else).
- Always pass `model: "cursor-grok-4.5-high"` explicitly on every `Task` tool call.

## Scope

- Applies to all subagent types: `generalPurpose`, `explore`, `debug`, `computerUse`, `videoReview`, `cursor-guide`, `bugbot`, `security-review`, `best-of-n-runner`, and any future types.
- Applies on cloud agents even if the parent agent is already Grok 4.5 High — still set the model explicitly.
- Does not restrict the parent cloud agent’s own model selection; it only constrains **spawned subagents**.

## If unavailable

- If `cursor-grok-4.5-high` cannot be used, **do not** fall back to another model.
- Skip spawning that subagent and continue the work yourself (or report that the subagent could not be started under policy).
